!! Opting a plugin into the settings hub

Create a `settings.tid` inside your plugin with any UI content:

```
title: $:/plugins/rimir/my-plugin/settings
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<div class="rr-input-row">
  <label>API Endpoint:</label>
  <$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/my-plugin/endpoint" tag="input" class="rr-input"/>
</div>
```

The hub transcludes this tiddler automatically when the user selects your plugin in the sidebar.

!! Plugin without settings

If your plugin has no configurable settings, the hub shows a fallback info card with a link to the plugin's documentation. No action needed — the fallback is automatic.

</$fill>
